LARKIN POE


Play all


        Rebecca & Megan Lovell started making music back when they were five years old in their hometown of Atlanta, GA taking music lessons and singing in a church. They formed a group and released music back when they were teenagers in 2005 along with their third sister as the Lovell Sisters until their disbandment in 2009. In 2010, the duo regrouped as LARKIN POE, which was the name of the sisters' great-great-great-grandfather, who was a distant cousin of Edgar Allan Poe.
    







 







