Steven Madden, Ltd. (NASDAQ:SHOO) Receives An Update From Brokers


 By Ashley Brown /  in  Stocks /  on  Wednesday, 26 Jul 2017 11:48 AM  / 0 Comments




Analysts reviewing Steven Madden, Ltd. have recently updated their recommended buy/sell ratings and price targets on the stock.  			         



Based on their most recently released notes to investors, 2 analysts have a rating of “buy”, 4 analysts “outperform”, 6 analysts “hold”, 0 analysts “underperform” and 0 analysts “sell”.
Ratings and price target breakdown:
 06/05/2017 – Steven Madden, Ltd. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Morgan Stanley. They now have a USD 38 price target on the stock.
 06/05/2017 – Steven Madden, Ltd. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Canaccord Genuity. They now have a USD 46 price target on the stock.
 06/01/2017 – Steven Madden, Ltd. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Piper Jaffray. They now have a USD 41 price target on the stock.
 04/24/2017 – Steven Madden, Ltd. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Citigroup. They now have a USD 45 price target on the stock.
 04/21/2017 – Steven Madden, Ltd. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Susquehanna. They now have a USD 44 price target on the stock.
 02/27/2017 – Steven Madden, Ltd. was upgraded to “” by analysts at B. Riley. They now have a USD 45 price target on the stock.
 01/03/2017 – Steven Madden, Ltd. was downgraded to “” by analysts at Jefferies. They now have a USD 37 price target on the stock.
 12/06/2016 – Wells Fargo began new coverage on Steven Madden, Ltd. giving the company a “” rating. They now have a USD 39 price target on the stock.
 08/03/2016 – Steven Madden, Ltd. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Telsey Advisory Group. They now have a USD 38 price target on the stock.
 07/18/2016 – Steven Madden, Ltd. was downgraded to “” by analysts at Buckingham Research. They now have a USD 36 price target on the stock.
 06/09/2016 – Steven Madden, Ltd. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at BB&T Capital Markets.
 04/22/2016 – Steven Madden, Ltd. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Sterne Agee. They now have a USD 45 price target on the stock.
 03/01/2016 – Steven Madden, Ltd. was downgraded to “” by analysts at Goldman Sachs. They now have a USD 27 price target on the stock.
 10/01/2015 – Steven Madden, Ltd. was upgraded to “” by analysts at Taglich Brothers. They now have a USD 44 price target on the stock.
 05/26/2015 – Steven Madden, Ltd. was downgraded to “” by analysts at Zacks.
Steven Madden, Ltd. has a 50 day moving average of 39.04 and a 200 day moving average of 37.54. The stock’s market capitalization is 2.44B, it has a 52-week low of 32.30 and a 52-week high of 41.35. 
The share price of the company (NASDAQ:SHOO) was up +2.88%, with a high of 41.35 during the day and the volume of Steven Madden, Ltd. shares traded was 601232.  



Steven Madden, Ltd. and its subsidiaries design, source, market and sell name brand and private label footwear for women, men and children, and name brand and private label fashion handbags and accessories. The Company operates through five segments: Wholesale Footwear, Wholesale Accessories, Retail, First Cost and Licensing. Its products are sold through its retail stores and e-commerce Websites within the United States, Canada, Mexico and South Africa, as well as department stores, specialty stores, luxury retailers, value priced retailers, national chains, merchants and catalog retailers. It provides merchandising support to its department store customers, including in-store fixtures and signage, supervision of displays and merchandising of its various product lines. Its brands include Madden Girl, Steve Madden Men’s, Madden, Steven, Stevies and Steve Madden Kids, Betsey Johnson, Superga, FREEBIRD by Steve, Report, Mad Love, Dolce Vita, Brian Atwood and Blondo.


